# app/static/js/

Client-side JavaScript for the site (runs in the browser).

## What belongs here
- Event handlers (click, submit, etc.)
- UI behaviour (show/hide, form validation, simple interactivity)
- Fetch calls to Flask endpoints (later, for dynamic features)

## What does NOT belong here
- Database access (DB stays server-side in Python)
- Secrets/credentials (never store secrets in JS)

## Pattern
If a page needs specific JS, either:
- Load a dedicated file for that page, or
- Keep it in `main.js` if it’s truly global

## User promo component
- Module: `app/static/js/components/userPromo.js`
- Exports:
	- `mountUserPromo(containerEl, userId, options?)`
	- `initUserPromos(root = document)`
- Auto-mount selector: `.js-user-promo[data-user-id]`
- Example markup:
	- `<div class="js-user-promo" data-user-id="42"></div>`

`initUserPromos()` is called from `app/static/js/pages/discover.js`.
